<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
The synonymisation of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Atriplex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Atriplex subsp. sect." order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Obione" species="tatarica" subSpecies="sect.">Atriplex sect. Obione</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. subsp. sect." pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="section" section="Sclerocalymma" species="tatarica" subSpecies="sect.">A. sect. Sclerocalymma</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. subsp. subsect." pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="subSection" species="tatarica" subSection="Argenteae" subSpecies="subsect.">A. subsect. Argenteae</taxonomicName>
is undertaken here for the first time. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Atriplex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Atriplex powellii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="powellii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Atriplex powellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
S.Watson, previously considered as a close relative of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. argentea" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="argentea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">A. argentea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Standley, PC" editor="Britton, NL" journalOrPublisher="21 (1). New York Botanical Garden, New York" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="1 - 93" refId="B23" refString="Standley, PC, 1916. Chenopodiaceae. In: Britton, NL, Ed., North American Flora, Vol. 21(1). New York Botanical Garden, New York: 1 - 93" title="Chenopodiaceae." volumeTitle="North American Flora, Vol." year="1916">Standley 1916</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Welsh, SL" journalOrPublisher="Rhodora" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="415 - 427" refId="B30" refString="Welsh, SL, 2001. Nomenclatural proposals in Atriplex (Chenopodiaceae). Rhodora 102: 415 - 427" title="Nomenclatural proposals in Atriplex (Chenopodiaceae)." volume="102" year="2001">Welsh 2001</bibRefCitation>
), occupies a distant phylogenetic position (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ppees.2022.125660" author="Zerdoner Calasan, A" journalOrPublisher="4. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" refId="B32" refString="Zerdoner Calasan, A, Hammen, S, Sukhorukov, AP, McDonald, JT, Brignone, NF, Boehnert, T, Kadereit, G, 2022. From continental Asia into the world: Global historical biogeography of the saltbush genus Atriplex (Chenopodieae, Chenopodioideae, Amaranthaceae). Perspectives in Plant Ecology, Evolution and Systematics 54: e125660. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ppees.2022.125660" title="From continental Asia into the world: Global historical biogeography of the saltbush genus Atriplex (Chenopodieae, Chenopodioideae, Amaranthaceae). Perspectives in Plant Ecology, Evolution and Systematics 54: e 125660." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ppees.2022.125660" year="2022">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Žerdoner">Zerdoner</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Čalasan">Calasan</normalizedToken>
et al. 2022
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
The name 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. subsp. sect." pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="section" section="Obione" species="argentea" subSpecies="sect.">A. sect. Obione</taxonomicName>
has usually been credited to 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyer, CA" editor="von Ledebour, CF" journalOrPublisher="4. G. Reimer, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="304 - 318" refId="B18" refString="Meyer, CA, 1833. Atriplex L. In: von Ledebour, CF, Meyer, CA, von Bunge, A, Eds., Flora Altaica, Vol. 4. G.Reimer, Berlin: 304 - 318" title="Atriplex L." volumeTitle="Flora Altaica, Vol." year="1833">Meyer (1833)</bibRefCitation>
, who accepted this subdivision in 'Flora 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Altaica’">Altaica'</normalizedToken>
. However, the first author who segregated this section within 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Atriplex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Atriplex" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Atriplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.127510" author="Reichenbach, HGL" journalOrPublisher="4. G. Reimer, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" refId="B20" refString="Reichenbach, HGL, 1828. Uebersicht des Gewaechs-Reichs in seinen natuerlichen Entwicklungsstufen. C. Cnobloch, Leipzig, 1-295. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.127510" title="Uebersicht des Gewaechs-Reichs in seinen natuerlichen Entwicklungsstufen. C. Cnobloch, Leipzig, 1 - 295." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.127510" year="1828">Reichenbach (1828)</bibRefCitation>
. He accepted the name and provided an indirect reference to the basionym as &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Obione" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Obione" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Obione</taxonomicName>
. G.&quot; The infrageneric taxa accepted by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.127510" author="Reichenbach, HGL" journalOrPublisher="4. G. Reimer, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" refId="B20" refString="Reichenbach, HGL, 1828. Uebersicht des Gewaechs-Reichs in seinen natuerlichen Entwicklungsstufen. C. Cnobloch, Leipzig, 1-295. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.127510" title="Uebersicht des Gewaechs-Reichs in seinen natuerlichen Entwicklungsstufen. C. Cnobloch, Leipzig, 1 - 295." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.127510" year="1828">Reichenbach (1828)</bibRefCitation>
were explicitly ranked as sections, as evidenced by a footnote on page 184 in this work. Similarly, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.19896" author="Hooker, JD" journalOrPublisher="197. Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" refId="B9" refString="Hooker, JD, 1870. The student's flora of the British Islands. Macmillan &amp; Co., London, 1-504. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.19896" title="The student's flora of the British Islands. Macmillan &amp; Co., London, 1 - 504." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.19896" year="1870">Hooker (1870)</bibRefCitation>
was the first to accept 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. (Obione) subsp. subgen." pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="subGenus" species="argentea" subGenus="Obione" subSpecies="subgen.">A. subgen. Obione</taxonomicName>
, which was explicitly ranked by him. On the contrary, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ascherson, PFA" journalOrPublisher="Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" refId="B3" refString="Ascherson, PFA, 1864. Flora der Provinz Brandenburg, der Altmark, und des Herzogthums Magdeburg, Vol. 1, part 2. A.Hirschwald, Berlin, 321-1034." title="Flora der Provinz Brandenburg, der Altmark, und des Herzogthums Magdeburg, Vol. 1, part 2. A. Hirschwald, Berlin, 321 - 1034." year="1864">Ascherson (1864)</bibRefCitation>
developed complex infrageneric systems that included at least three ranks, with names at all of these ranks, and made no note of their ranking; such classifications are to be treated as unranked (Art. 37.3).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
